-- German Managers Propose Voluntary Pay Caps, Handelsblatt Reports
-- B y   J a n a   R a n d o w
-- 2012-04-23T07:46:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-23/german-managers-propose-voluntary-pay-caps-handelsblatt-reports.html
The chairmen of the supervisory
boards of Commerzbank AG and Deutsche Boerse AG are proposing to
limit compensation for board members to prevent changes in
regulation or laws aimed at compensation,  Handelsblatt  newspaper
reported.  Klaus-Peter Mueller and Manfred Gentz suggested to
voluntarily include upper limits or pay caps in board members’
contracts, the newspaper said, citing a letter to the chairmen
of the supervisory boards of all companies represented in
 Germany ’s DAX index.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jana Randow in Frankfurt at 
